  "text": "with (., .) the inner product. The filter masks ft (taken as a vector) usually describe an over-complete set of Haar wavelet filters, which are generated by varying particular geometric parameters, such as, their relative position (a, b), width w and height h (see Figure 3 for an example). An optimal subset of those wavelets, as well as the weights C y t and classifier thresholds Bt are obtained from the AdaBoost training algorithm [CITATION_1] .",
